ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v281.group

Class BAR_P05_VISIT

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v281.group.BAR_P05_VISIT
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class BAR_P05_VISIT
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a BAR_P05_VISIT group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: PV1 (Patient Visit) optional
    • 2: PV2 (Patient Visit - Additional Information) optional
    • 3: PRT (Participation Information) optional repeating
    • 4: ROL (Role) optional repeating
    • 5: DB1 (Disability) optional repeating
    • 6: OBX (Observation/Result) optional repeating
    • 7: AL1 (Patient Allergy Information) optional repeating
    • 8: DG1 (Diagnosis) optional repeating
    • 9: DRG (Diagnosis Related Group) optional
    • 10: BAR_P05_PROCEDURE (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 11: GT1 (Guarantor) optional repeating
    • 12: NK1 (Next of Kin / Associated Parties) optional repeating
    • 13: BAR_P05_INSURANCE (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 14: ACC (Accident) optional
    • 15: UB1 () optional
    • 16: UB2 (Uniform Billing Data) optional
    • 17: ABS (Abstract) optional
    • 18: BLC (Blood Code) optional repeating
    • 19: RMI (Risk Management Incident) optional
    See Also:
